<node id="China">
  <data key="d0">China</data>
  <data key="d1">location</data>
  <data key="d2">China is a significant market and participant in global trade, contributing to the net revenue of various companies. It holds a 30% share in 2025 and is a major location for the expansion of display manufacturing facilities. A substantial portion of customers and suppliers are based in China, which plays a crucial role in the supply chain due to its export of certain technologies, materials, and rare earth minerals. However, China faces restrictions on exporting certain products, impacting companies like NVIDIA and their operations, due to United States government export regulations. The country is also a geopolitical entity that may contribute to heightened risks of cybersecurity attacks due to ongoing tensions and conflicts. Companies must ensure compliance with export controls when shipping products to China.

China has seen a decrease in revenues, contributing to a 4% decrease in total revenues. The region contributed to the company's revenues, with a decrease from 43% to 33% of total revenues between fiscal 2024 and 2025. The inability to obtain export licenses has affected the company's operations, including reducing backlog and returning deposits from customers. China is a jurisdiction where the company has significant operations and from which the company may derive revenues, but also faces challenges such as trade restrictions and potential refunds for prepayments.

China is a country where certain companies are involved in advanced semiconductor manufacturing and are affected by the U.S. Entity List and BIS Rules. The country is a location where the company has significant manufacturing operations. China is a major region for manufacturing of legacy node logic and memory chips and is the world’s largest consumer of ICs. It is a significant market for the company, where the inability to obtain export licenses could affect customer support and product supply. China is a significant geographic region for the company's revenues, with a notable percentage of total sales. The country is a significant revenue contributor, accounting for a large percentage of total revenues in both the three and six-month periods ended December 31, 2024 and 2023. Customers in China increased investments in semiconductors to become more self-sufficient, affecting the company's revenue.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f0b30e55c2d2c942c8ef27807467b3d6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e7481c513c84b894dbf5566a03c9c31d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f50e3434e5c216500628bf58a9da4be1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-158df076948257685462bdd5a2ffcd95&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-625ca1cf50e3b24380c8601c96bdd7a3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-85c73190292489fe36964fdd5fc32b0c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5d99a02cc7061af948a4068d7dfaf580&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cf53d552d1955a280cebbd6e2d050c2d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1b0f36135b3b08cac0302bf342d7918d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7d8ee469fd420dd945b64b580faff532&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4cef59817c38511355f56938f73f6db2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-da2b01ab4070bbe76a7dd3d4ffb383d7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c0f7533f1c0231555ac5ae30f4d37842&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-120a4f2fbe48d0891e48fba271c88ec1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-69ff95667fb52350500821b847289ef6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f20aa9a81d6ab585196c52c4b81c36f5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b7969877a8fd0841863c700fea233da5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d5d617bafedeb6760bbc60c5e3993fb7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1329332311e82d0b2cc6f7232bfaa092&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d780eacfb91e291d22055bf3aca31fa3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-db3fcbe26ec52d22abad5f9f0435fea6</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
