<node id="One Big Beautiful Bill Act">
  <data key="d0">One Big Beautiful Bill Act</data>
  <data key="d1">event</data>
  <data key="d2">The One Big Beautiful Bill Act (OBBBA) was enacted into law in July 2025 and contains changes to key U.S. federal income tax laws.&lt;SEP&gt;The One Big Beautiful Bill Act is legislation that has affected the realization of CAMT credits and the valuation of deferred tax assets.&lt;SEP&gt;The One Big Beautiful Bill Act is legislation that has affected the realization of corporate alternative minimum tax credits.&gt;&lt;SEP&gt;The One Big Beautiful Bill Act, enacted on July 4, 2025, includes tax reform provisions such as full expensing of domestic research costs and increasing the investment tax credit for certain investments in domestic semiconductor manufacturing from 25% to 35%.&lt;SEP&gt;The One Big Beautiful Bill Act is a legislation that affects the tax deductions for U.S. tax purposes and influences the organization's tax planning and valuation allowances.&lt;SEP&gt;The One Big Beautiful Bill Act (OBBBA) is a legislation enacted by the U.S. government that affects the organization's ability to use deferred tax assets.&lt;SEP&gt;The One Big Beautiful Bill Act is legislation that introduced several permanent changes to the United States tax code, affecting how U.S. multinational corporations are taxed.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-db98b1c09ec551c8a83f9131498334c6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f50e3434e5c216500628bf58a9da4be1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-217dcca296bd42c2a1d26c339d20ff32&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-528b15deb865d055e3be525ecf5963bc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ae71f5af8c77cdfb1dcf9e739c3e7b9c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7200d8553fd2e4a1586cd2f8af4129fc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a296116922ea376dbdc0f563507f5547</data>
