<node id="Common Stock">
  <data key="d0">Common Stock</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Common stock represents the financial instrument that the company repurchases in the market.&lt;SEP&gt;Common Stock refers to the class of ownership in a company that provides investors with voting rights and potential for capital appreciation.&lt;SEP&gt;Common stock represents the class of equity security that represents ownership in a company and is subject to market price fluctuations.&lt;SEP&gt;Common Stock refers to the class of shares that INTC has authorized for repurchase.|&lt;SEP&gt;Common Stock refers to the shares of the company that can be repurchased by the company itself.|&lt;SEP&gt;The common stock represents the company's equity that is traded in the market and is subject to volatility.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-a36df99dfa3a16bd8e4d429df7cf42a6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b976a275590777e7877d2d66b5f6379c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-625ca1cf50e3b24380c8601c96bdd7a3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f60be1d369008dda0461cefaf2ff61fa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-01ee832930ff813d9db8fa5bfa02507e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6295c9841b489759670dace2137e3d9a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-541097656a29c150756d08c4943ad8b0</data>
