</node>
<node id="Gross Profit">
  <data key="d0">Gross Profit</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Gross profit is a financial metric representing total net revenue less the cost of revenue, which decreased from 75.0% to 71.1% for NVIDIA in fiscal year 2026.&lt;SEP&gt;Gross Profit is the profit after deducting the cost of goods sold from revenue, amounting to $3,435 in 2026 and $3,496 in 2025.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-dd5f5a1a7c540b1c8cafe05b35cfd7fb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-43a8f055527dad4e87136bbd01caf743</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777261185</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Gross Margin">
  <data key="d0">Gross Margin</data>
  <data key="d1">financialmetric</data>
  <data key="d2">Gross margin is a financial ratio that decreased for NVIDIA from 75.0% to 71.1% in fiscal year 2026 due to a change in business model and a significant charge related to H20 inventory.&lt;SEP&gt;The gross margin is a financial metric that represents the percentage of revenue remaining after deducting the cost of goods sold.&lt;SEP&gt;Gross Margin is a financial metric that represents the percentage of revenue remaining after deducting the costs of revenues, expressed as a percentage.&lt;SEP&gt;Gross Margin is a financial metric that fluctuates with revenue levels and product mix and is affected by variations in costs related to manufacturing and servicing products.&lt;SEP&gt;Gross Margin is a financial metric that fluctuates with revenue levels and product mix, affected by manufacturing and servicing costs, and the company's ability to scale operations efficiently.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-dd5f5a1a7c540b1c8cafe05b35cfd7fb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fe1fafd9b0c6f09af84ad373757a9b00&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-37906de44c22f23501372f2b90cd5aa7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-da2b01ab4070bbe76a7dd3d4ffb383d7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c0f7533f1c0231555ac5ae30f4d37842&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e28f2689bd6a5fe65b47f7c31f1a8adc</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777307810</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Fiscal Year 2026">
  <data key="d0">Fiscal Year 2026</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Fiscal Year 2026 is the most recent fiscal year for which NVIDIA reported financial data, including a decrease in gross margins and revenue growth in specific segments.&lt;SEP&gt;Fiscal Year 2026 is a period during which the company spent $6.1 billion on capital expenditures.&lt;SEP&gt;Fiscal Year 2026 is the financial year starting on or after July 1, 2025, and ending on or before June 30, 2026, relevant for the implementation of new accounting standards.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-dd5f5a1a7c540b1c8cafe05b35cfd7fb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-91ba0c40d4695fe5428e9f1aaee99693&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-528b15deb865d055e3be525ecf5963bc</data>
