  <data key="d3">chunk-3f2ce3a4f3492cdc62d91339c8332500&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3f659a7f219f7f617d5e8dc482fab75d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8e2d85f7a44ae4d46a5296c95183929c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-37906de44c22f23501372f2b90cd5aa7</data>
  <data key="d2">Deferred Tax Assets and Liabilities are part of the company's income tax calculations in the U.S. and foreign jurisdictions.&lt;SEP&gt;Income Taxes refers to the taxes the Company is subject to in the United Kingdom and other foreign jurisdictions, accounted for using the asset and liability method under GAAP.&gt;&lt;SEP&gt;Income taxes represent the taxes paid by the Company on its income, subject to complex tax laws and regulations.</data>
