<node id="Export Regulations">
  <data key="d0">Export Regulations</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Export regulations are laws implemented by the United States government that limit the provision of certain products and services to customers outside the U.S., including in China.&lt;SEP&gt;Export Regulations are the legal requirements and restrictions that control the shipment of goods and services out of a country.&lt;SEP&gt;Export regulations are a type of government action that can affect AMD's international business activities.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e7481c513c84b894dbf5566a03c9c31d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-85c73190292489fe36964fdd5fc32b0c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-737963f5a4aa4c7ac5ff75bd66cabe60</data>
