<node id="Fiscal 2025">
  <data key="d0">Fiscal 2025</data>
  <data key="d1">timeperiod</data>
  <data key="d2">Fiscal 2025 is a financial period during which the company's net revenue, gross margin, operating income, operating margin, net income, and earnings per diluted share were reported.&lt;SEP&gt;Fiscal 2025 is the fiscal year in which the organization recorded a full valuation allowance against the CAMT credit deferred tax asset, affecting its effective tax rate and provision for income taxes.&lt;SEP&gt;Fiscal 2025 is the fiscal year during which Applied Materials, Inc. announced a workforce reduction plan and new tax incentive agreements in Singapore.&lt;SEP&gt;Fiscal 2025 is the period in which the company identified goodwill impairment charges in the PCB and Component Inspection reportable segment and assessed tangible and purchased intangible assets for impairment.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e7481c513c84b894dbf5566a03c9c31d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7200d8553fd2e4a1586cd2f8af4129fc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3a29194982b15aafff922b31789e91ea&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1329332311e82d0b2cc6f7232bfaa092</data>
