<node id="Artificial Intelligence">
  <data key="d0">Artificial Intelligence</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Artificial Intelligence is the field of computer science that aims to create intelligent machines capable of human-like intelligence.&gt;&lt;SEP&gt;Artificial Intelligence is a technology that can be used to create more effective phishing emails or social engineering attacks and exploit vulnerabilities in electronic security programs.&lt;SEP&gt;Artificial Intelligence is a concept central to the operations of both AMD and Meta, as they both aim to accelerate AI innovation and provide AI-powered services and experiences.&lt;SEP&gt;Artificial Intelligence is a concept related to technology that involves the development of intelligent machines.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f50e3434e5c216500628bf58a9da4be1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-158df076948257685462bdd5a2ffcd95&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7d8ee469fd420dd945b64b580faff532&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3d5354b5fb76e945ee44e3cc730cae08&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e3082390d4ae9b34c69f94e2ec0135c5</data>
