<node id="Korea">
  <data key="d0">Korea</data>
  <data key="d1">location</data>
  <data key="d2">Korea is a geographic region that contributed to the net revenue of the company, with a 20% share in 2025.&gt;&lt;SEP&gt;Korea is a country where the company has substantial business operations and customer base.&lt;SEP&gt;Korea is a significant market for the business and part of the geographical concentration of the customer base.&lt;SEP&gt;Korea is a region contributing to the company's revenues, with 12%, 9%, and 18% of total revenues in fiscal years 2025, 2024, and 2023, respectively.&lt;SEP&gt;Korea is a geographic region mentioned as a source of semiconductor manufacturers investing in China.&lt;SEP&gt;Korea is a region contributing to the company's revenues, though with a smaller percentage compared to China and Taiwan.&lt;SEP&gt;Korea is a location that contributes to the total revenues, with a percentage of total revenues during the specified periods.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f50e3434e5c216500628bf58a9da4be1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-85c73190292489fe36964fdd5fc32b0c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1b0f36135b3b08cac0302bf342d7918d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7d8ee469fd420dd945b64b580faff532&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-da2b01ab4070bbe76a7dd3d4ffb383d7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b7969877a8fd0841863c700fea233da5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1329332311e82d0b2cc6f7232bfaa092&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-db3fcbe26ec52d22abad5f9f0435fea6</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777307808</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Taiwan">
  <data key="d0">Taiwan</data>
  <data key="d1">location</data>
  <data key="d2">Taiwan is a significant geographic region for a company's revenues, contributing substantially to its financial performance. In 2025, Taiwan accounted for 24% of the company's net revenue, making it a crucial part of the company's financial success. The region is also a key contributor to the company's total revenues, with 27% in 2025 and 18% in 2024. Taiwan is part of the geographical concentration of the company's customer base, and the company delivers a significant portion of its products and services there. Increased investments in process control in Taiwan have contributed to the company's overall revenue increase in fiscal year 2025. Semiconductor manufacturers from Taiwan have also invested in China, further highlighting the region's importance. As the second largest revenue contributor during the periods mentioned, Taiwan plays a vital role in the company's growth and success.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f50e3434e5c216500628bf58a9da4be1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-85c73190292489fe36964fdd5fc32b0c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1b0f36135b3b08cac0302bf342d7918d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7d8ee469fd420dd945b64b580faff532&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-da2b01ab4070bbe76a7dd3d4ffb383d7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c0f7533f1c0231555ac5ae30f4d37842&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b7969877a8fd0841863c700fea233da5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d5d617bafedeb6760bbc60c5e3993fb7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1329332311e82d0b2cc6f7232bfaa092&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-db3fcbe26ec52d22abad5f9f0435fea6</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777307830</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Japan">
  <data key="d0">Japan</data>
  <data key="d1">location</data>
