</node>
<node id="Real Property and Improvements">
  <data key="d0">Real Property and Improvements</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Real Property and Improvements are physical assets that include land and buildings, which the company invests in as part of its capital expenditures.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b976a275590777e7877d2d66b5f6379c</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777259232</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Demonstration and Testing Equipment">
  <data key="d0">Demonstration and Testing Equipment</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Demonstration and Testing Equipment refers to the tools and machinery used by the company for product demonstrations and quality testing, included in capital expenditures.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b976a275590777e7877d2d66b5f6379c</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777259232</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Manufacturing and Network Equipment">
  <data key="d0">Manufacturing and Network Equipment</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Manufacturing and Network Equipment includes the machinery and infrastructure used in the production and networking processes of the company, part of capital expenditures.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b976a275590777e7877d2d66b5f6379c</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777259232</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Senior Notes">
  <data key="d0">Senior Notes</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Senior Notes are a type of debt obligation issued by a company, representing an aggregate principal amount of unsecured debt with varying due dates as detailed in the company's financial statements. They have a higher claim on assets in the event of bankruptcy and are part of the company's financing activities. These debt instruments have varying maturity dates ranging from fiscal year 2029 to fiscal year 2063, and the entity has an aggregate principal debt obligation on them. Senior Notes are also related to the company's capital structure and indebtedness, with an outstanding indebtedness of $5.95 billion consisting of unsecured long-term notes. In certain conditions, such as rating downgrades, the company may be required to repurchase these financial instruments. An example of a Senior Note issuance is the $750.0 million in February 2024. Overall, Senior Notes are senior, unsecured notes with an aggregate principal amount of $5.95 billion.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b976a275590777e7877d2d66b5f6379c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bfac3dde6482c2f8fd9ea0e0c659c15b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bb113ac9e0cc9e74e5cc817ec0cd9a79&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6e39760d10a53b7326a952678788b4f5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f8cb9583c9766314f3cbadb2fe74821b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d34b219513d1d4953f831b7693287834&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fcbd467e0d3d2d1e90e50929e4ef4372&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8fa5ffd55eec85058d06665add3afcd3</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777307860</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Tax Withholding Payments">
  <data key="d0">Tax Withholding Payments</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Tax Withholding Payments are the amounts withheld by the company for tax purposes on behalf of employees, especially related to equity awards, and are part of financing activities.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b976a275590777e7877d2d66b5f6379c</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777259232</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Employee Stock Purchase Plan">
  <data key="d0">Employee Stock Purchase Plan</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">The Employee Stock Purchase Plan allows employees to buy company stock at a discount, which affects the company's financing activities.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b976a275590777e7877d2d66b5f6379c</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777259232</data>
