<node id="Joint Ventures">
  <data key="d0">Joint Ventures</data>
  <data key="d1">event</data>
  <data key="d2">Joint Ventures are companies formed in collaboration between two or more parties, which may decline in value or fail to meet objectives.&lt;SEP&gt;Joint ventures are business collaborations that can impact AMD's operations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-99b76900a97d7c959bc5ca885c3601da&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-737963f5a4aa4c7ac5ff75bd66cabe60</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777261366</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Strategic Investments">
  <data key="d0">Strategic Investments</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Strategic Investments are investments made to achieve specific business objectives, which may fail to commercialize technologies.&lt;SEP&gt;Strategic Investments are investments made in companies, technologies, or products to achieve specific business objectives, which can lead to risks such as diversion of management's attention and disruption of ongoing businesses.&lt;SEP&gt;Strategic Investments are investments made by Applied Materials, Inc. that result in realized and unrealized gains or losses, impacting the company's net income.&lt;SEP&gt;Strategic investments are external growth strategies that Arm makes, which come with risks associated with managing the growth effectively.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-99b76900a97d7c959bc5ca885c3601da&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-158df076948257685462bdd5a2ffcd95&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3a29194982b15aafff922b31789e91ea&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a09335734e89edd5d8f3e04bd3466cd8</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777308127</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="New Markets">
  <data key="d0">New Markets</data>
  <data key="d1">location</data>
  <data key="d2">New Markets are areas where the company may not have a strong market position or customer relationships, and where competitors may be more established.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-99b76900a97d7c959bc5ca885c3601da</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777260109</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Foreign Jurisdictions">
  <data key="d0">Foreign Jurisdictions</data>
  <data key="d1">location</data>
  <data key="d2">Foreign Jurisdictions are locations outside the United States where the company is also subject to income taxes and changing tax laws.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-99b76900a97d7c959bc5ca885c3601da</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777260109</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Intellectual Property Rights">
  <data key="d0">Intellectual Property Rights</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Intellectual property rights are legal rights that protect creations of the mind, and their protection is crucial for the company and its customers.&lt;SEP&gt;Intellectual property rights, including patents, trade secrets, copyrights, are vital for protecting technology and are subject to infringement risks.&lt;SEP&gt;Intellectual Property Rights refer to the company's ability to obtain and protect key technologies, which is crucial for its operations and competitive advantage.&lt;SEP&gt;Intellectual Property Rights are legal rights to intangible assets such as patents, trademarks, and copyrights, which may not be adequately protected in certain countries.&lt;SEP&gt;Intellectual property rights are proprietary rights that Arm has to protect, particularly its products and brand, which involves costs and potential litigation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-99b76900a97d7c959bc5ca885c3601da&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5d99a02cc7061af948a4068d7dfaf580&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cf53d552d1955a280cebbd6e2d050c2d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-120a4f2fbe48d0891e48fba271c88ec1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a09335734e89edd5d8f3e04bd3466cd8</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777308127</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Internal Financial Controls">
  <data key="d0">Internal Financial Controls</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Internal Financial Controls are the systems and procedures used by an acquired company to manage financial risks and ensure compliance with regulations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-99b76900a97d7c959bc5ca885c3601da</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777260109</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Cybersecurity">
  <data key="d0">Cybersecurity</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Cybersecurity pertains to the protection of an acquired company's digital assets and the prevention of cyber threats, which is essential for safeguarding sensitive information.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-99b76900a97d7c959bc5ca885c3601da</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777260109</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Privacy Policies">
  <data key="d0">Privacy Policies</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Privacy Policies are the guidelines and rules that govern how an acquired company manages, protects, and processes personal data, ensuring compliance with data protection laws.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-99b76900a97d7c959bc5ca885c3601da</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777260109</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Compliance Programs">
  <data key="d0">Compliance Programs</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Compliance Programs are the initiatives and measures taken by an acquired company to ensure adherence to laws, regulations, and internal policies.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-99b76900a97d7c959bc5ca885c3601da</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777260109</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Trade Control Processes">
  <data key="d0">Trade Control Processes</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Trade Control Processes are the mechanisms and procedures that an acquired company uses to manage international trade, ensuring compliance with export control laws and regulations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-99b76900a97d7c959bc5ca885c3601da</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777260109</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Environmental Health and Safety">
  <data key="d0">Environmental Health and Safety</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Environmental Health and Safety refers to the policies and practices that an acquired company implements to minimize its environmental impact and ensure the safety and health of its employees.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-99b76900a97d7c959bc5ca885c3601da</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777260109</data>
