</node>
<node id="Anti-Corruption">
  <data key="d0">Anti-Corruption</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Anti-Corruption pertains to the policies and measures that an acquired company adopts to prevent bribery, corruption, and unethical business practices.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-99b76900a97d7c959bc5ca885c3601da</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777260109</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Human Resource Policies">
  <data key="d0">Human Resource Policies</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Human Resource Policies are the guidelines and rules that an acquired company follows in managing its workforce, including recruitment, compensation, and employee relations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-99b76900a97d7c959bc5ca885c3601da</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777260109</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Intellectual Property Laws">
  <data key="d0">Intellectual Property Laws</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Intellectual Property Laws are legal frameworks that govern the protection and enforcement of intellectual property rights, which may impact the ability to protect these rights and increase costs and uncertainties for businesses.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-158df076948257685462bdd5a2ffcd95</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777260109</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Patent Applications">
  <data key="d0">Patent Applications</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Patent Applications are formal requests made to a patent office for granting a patent for an invention, which can be affected by changes in intellectual property laws and their interpretation.&lt;SEP&gt;Pending patent applications that the company has filed, seeking protection for some of its products and technologies.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-158df076948257685462bdd5a2ffcd95&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c3b4f2c79e964eb1c327adb0e6e96fea</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777307375</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Third-Party Intellectual Property">
  <data key="d0">Third-Party Intellectual Property</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Third-Party Intellectual Property refers to intellectual property rights owned by entities other than the company, which the company may need to use on commercially reasonable terms to avoid adverse impacts on its business.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-158df076948257685462bdd5a2ffcd95</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777260109</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Cybersecurity Threats">
  <data key="d0">Cybersecurity Threats</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Cybersecurity Threats are potential vulnerabilities, attacks, or breaches that target information technology systems with the aim of stealing, corrupting, or otherwise compromising data and information.&lt;SEP&gt;Cybersecurity Threats are risks that threaten the confidentiality, integrity, and availability of KLA's IT Systems and Confidential Information, originating from diverse threat actors and attack vectors.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-158df076948257685462bdd5a2ffcd95&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e74b16856b8a1a3ddf8e77f75d7175ed</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777307375</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Information Technology Systems">
  <data key="d0">Information Technology Systems</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Information Technology Systems are the computer and telecommunications systems used to collect, use, transmit, store, and process data, which are subject to disruptions, outages, failures, and security breaches or incidents.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-158df076948257685462bdd5a2ffcd95</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777260109</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Confidential Information">
  <data key="d0">Confidential Information</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Confidential Information is sensitive data that is not publicly available and belongs to the company, its customers, or other business partners, which needs to be protected from unauthorized access or misuse.&lt;SEP&gt;Confidential Information includes confidential data, transactional data, IP, and personal information of individuals associated with KLA, its customers, and business partners.&lt;SEP&gt;Confidential Information refers to sensitive data that requires protection and restoration efforts, and is critical for business operations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-158df076948257685462bdd5a2ffcd95&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-adf3cdd028d63a6900c51e0d73fc800e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e74b16856b8a1a3ddf8e77f75d7175ed</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777307374</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Personal Information">
  <data key="d0">Personal Information</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Personal Information is data that can be used to identify an individual, which is collected and processed by the company and is subject to protection under privacy and data protection laws.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-158df076948257685462bdd5a2ffcd95</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777260109</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Third-Party Providers">
  <data key="d0">Third-Party Providers</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Third-party providers supply AI capabilities, and reliance on them is crucial for the successful implementation of AI in business operations.&lt;SEP&gt;Third-Party Providers are external organizations that own and maintain systems used by the company for data processing, which may be involved in cybersecurity incidents.&lt;SEP&gt;Third-Party Providers are external organizations that provide services and products, including IT systems, to KLA and are involved in the collection, use, transmission, and storage of Confidential Information.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-158df076948257685462bdd5a2ffcd95&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5d99a02cc7061af948a4068d7dfaf580&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e74b16856b8a1a3ddf8e77f75d7175ed</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777307375</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Global Supply Chain">
  <data key="d0">Global Supply Chain</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The Global Supply Chain is the network of suppliers and partners involved in the production and distribution of goods and services, which can be indirectly affected by cybersecurity incidents.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-158df076948257685462bdd5a2ffcd95</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777260109</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Threat Actors">
  <data key="d0">Threat Actors</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Threat Actors are individuals or groups that attempt to gain unauthorized access to information systems or data, potentially supported by state actors, and may use various techniques and technologies to carry out attacks.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-158df076948257685462bdd5a2ffcd95</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777260109</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Russia">
  <data key="d0">Russia</data>
  <data key="d1">location</data>
  <data key="d2">Russia is a geopolitical entity that may contribute to heightened risks of cybersecurity attacks due to ongoing tensions and conflicts.&lt;SEP&gt;Russia is a country involved in a war with Ukraine, leading to international sanctions.&lt;SEP&gt;Russia is a country in conflict with Ukraine, affecting international businesses and markets.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-158df076948257685462bdd5a2ffcd95&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d5dab522fff7a5a27ab17d42eb8613b8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6430e92774e5a3f258ef2544910d4dd5</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777307810</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Middle East">
  <data key="d0">Middle East</data>
  <data key="d1">location</data>
  <data key="d2">The Middle East is a geopolitical region that may contribute to heightened risks of cybersecurity attacks due to ongoing tensions and conflicts.&lt;SEP&gt;The Middle East is a region where military conflicts and geopolitical tensions have occurred, impacting the company's operations and business.&lt;SEP&gt;The Middle East is a region experiencing hostilities and military activity, impacting global businesses.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-158df076948257685462bdd5a2ffcd95&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-120a4f2fbe48d0891e48fba271c88ec1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6430e92774e5a3f258ef2544910d4dd5</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777307810</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Quantum Computing">
  <data key="d0">Quantum Computing</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Quantum Computing is a technology with the potential to undermine current encryption standards and allow threat actors to circumvent existing protective measures.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-158df076948257685462bdd5a2ffcd95</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777260109</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Cross-Border Data Transfer">
  <data key="d0">Cross-Border Data Transfer</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Cross-Border Data Transfer is the process of moving data across national borders, which is subject to developing restrictions and may result in significant compliance costs for businesses.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-158df076948257685462bdd5a2ffcd95</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777260109</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Data Localization">
  <data key="d0">Data Localization</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Data Localization is the storage and processing of data within a specific geographic area, which is subject to developing restrictions and may result in significant compliance costs for businesses.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-158df076948257685462bdd5a2ffcd95</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777260109</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Business Combinations">
  <data key="d0">Business Combinations</data>
  <data key="d1">event</data>
  <data key="d2">Business Combinations refer to the process of merging or consolidating businesses, which involves numerous risks to the company's financial condition and operations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-158df076948257685462bdd5a2ffcd95</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777260109</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Acquisitions">
  <data key="d0">Acquisitions</data>
  <data key="d1">event</data>
  <data key="d2">Acquisitions refer to the process where one company purchases or takes over another, leading to various outcomes and impacts on the acquiring company. This business event can result in goodwill and intangible assets for the acquiring company, as well as incremental charges such as amortization of purchased intangible assets. Acquisitions can also impact a company's operations and its ability to integrate new businesses, as seen in the case of AMD. They are an important element of a company's strategy, involving the pursuit and integration of new technologies and businesses from external sources. However, acquisitions come with risks, including failure to realize expected revenues and returns from the acquired businesses, as well as the challenges of managing growth effectively, as demonstrated by Arm's external growth strategies. Additionally, acquisitions can lead to a more concentrated customer base, which may pose further risks and considerations for the acquiring company. Overall, acquisitions are a complex aspect of corporate strategy that can have significant financial and operational implications for the companies involved.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-158df076948257685462bdd5a2ffcd95&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-625ca1cf50e3b24380c8601c96bdd7a3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-531a2d4da0efcbaa075b41456e2d3536&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3a29194982b15aafff922b31789e91ea&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-737963f5a4aa4c7ac5ff75bd66cabe60&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-adf3cdd028d63a6900c51e0d73fc800e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b07cc11b6e49549f800863a0e198d15c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a09335734e89edd5d8f3e04bd3466cd8</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777308178</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Divestitures">
  <data key="d0">Divestitures</data>
  <data key="d1">event</data>
  <data key="d2">Divestitures are the selling of a subsidiary or other business unit, which can be associated with risks such as the inability to complete proposed transactions timely or at all.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-158df076948257685462bdd5a2ffcd95</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777260109</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Goodwill">
  <data key="d0">Goodwill</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Goodwill represents the excess of the purchase price over the fair value of net assets acquired in a business combination and is periodically reviewed for impairment.&lt;SEP&gt;Goodwill is an intangible asset representing the future economic benefits arising from potential synergies of acquired companies, amounting to $3,707 in both 2026 and 2025.&lt;SEP&gt;Goodwill is recorded as the excess of consideration transferred over the acquisition-date fair values of assets acquired and liabilities assumed.&gt;&lt;SEP&gt;Goodwill represents the intangible assets of a company, which may need to be written off in case of poor business performance or acquisition issues.&lt;SEP&gt;Goodwill represents the excess of costs over the net fair value of net assets acquired in a business combination and is tested for impairment at least annually.&lt;SEP&gt;Goodwill is an intangible asset representing the future economic benefits arising from assets acquired in a business combination that are not individually identified and separately recognized.&lt;SEP&gt;Goodwill is an intangible asset representing the future economic benefits arising from assets acquired in a business combination.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-625ca1cf50e3b24380c8601c96bdd7a3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-43a8f055527dad4e87136bbd01caf743&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8e2d85f7a44ae4d46a5296c95183929c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-adf3cdd028d63a6900c51e0d73fc800e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-25056dc4aba0a40a47c338bbf9630c33&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-706c3addabed1cbc496a03d35fbb0b1b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d780eacfb91e291d22055bf3aca31fa3</data>
