<node id="Securities Exchange Act of 1934">
  <data key="d0">Securities Exchange Act of 1934</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The Securities Exchange Act of 1934 is a significant piece of legislation that defines Rule 16a-1(f) and is relevant to AMD's trading arrangements.&lt;SEP&gt;The Securities Exchange Act of 1934 is a legislation under which AMD's directors and officers are defined and must report their trading activities, including Rule 10b5-1 trading plans.&lt;SEP&gt;The Securities Exchange Act of 1934 is a law that amends the Securities Act of 1933 and includes provisions for forward-looking statements.</data>
