<node id="Rule 10b5-1">
  <data key="d0">Rule 10b5-1</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Rule 10b5-1 is a regulation that allows company insiders to set up pre-arranged trading plans to satisfy the affirmative defense of the rule.&lt;SEP&gt;Rule 10b5-1 is a regulation under which INTC's directors and officers may enter into trading plans for the purchase or sale of company shares.|&lt;SEP&gt;Rule 10b5-1 is a trading arrangement rule under the Exchange Act that allows directors and officers to enter into plans for the purchase or sale of shares.|&lt;SEP&gt;Rule 10b5-1 is a regulation under the Exchange Act that allows directors and officers to enter into trading plans for buying or selling company shares.|&lt;SEP&gt;Rule 10b5-1 is a regulation under the Exchange Act that allows directors and officers to enter into trading plans for shares.|</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-42b87cf93df46f504c0e370bbcbc6d94&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f60be1d369008dda0461cefaf2ff61fa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c4845686f7704c5c80e402305d19f7ce&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-77d86694dce1fc1e9c3d3ac3bab4c5be&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-01ee832930ff813d9db8fa5bfa02507e</data>
