<node id="Arm">
  <data key="d0">Arm</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Arm is a company that provides technology and services for the development of various computing devices, from sensors to supercomputers.&lt;SEP&gt;Arm is a company that designs and licenses technology for semiconductors, with a focus on advanced products and subsystems.&lt;SEP&gt;Arm is a technology company that has confirmed commercial momentum with various partners and is expanding its compute platform into silicon with the Arm AGI CPU.&lt;SEP&gt;Arm is a company that has AGI CPU and ongoing CSS investments, strengthening the Arm ecosystem for AI and cloud workloads.&lt;SEP&gt;Arm is a company that develops compute subsystems, chiplets, and System-on-a-Chip (SoC) solutions, and is involved in licensing agreements and semiconductor electronics industries. It also faces various risks and challenges, including reliance on a limited number of customers, management of growth, and data security.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-5068f4b1da4cd023617e872a463eeb62&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9fe18d577f076ce03948540ed8563a5c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a09335734e89edd5d8f3e04bd3466cd8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e303b18ab63b26668de99eef62a26b7e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0fc487cdc1541b708566fbf837bf0441</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777308126</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
