<node id="Arm China">
  <data key="d0">Arm China</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Arm China is a company with which an agreement for software engineering-related services was terminated, leading to disposal expenses.&lt;SEP&gt;Arm China is a customer from which the company derives revenue and in which it has an equity method investment.&lt;SEP&gt;Arm China is a related party that sublicenses Arm's processor technology, particularly in the PRC market.&lt;SEP&gt;Arm China is an organization that provides financial information to the IPLA and is involved in transactions that may be affected by political actions and export control regulations.&gt;</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-5068f4b1da4cd023617e872a463eeb62&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8b7994a7b9c5c9289cc48f3afe48287c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d028a96cd827e54a97bfc99b9a77942a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ca207bb382651453029b45cb72e9feff</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777262483</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="IPLA">
  <data key="d0">IPLA</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">The IPLA is an agreement that governs the sublicensing rights and revenue sharing between Arm and Arm China.&lt;SEP&gt;The IPLA is an organization that has financial dealings with Arm China, relying on the financial information provided by Arm China for determining payments due.&gt;</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-5068f4b1da4cd023617e872a463eeb62&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d028a96cd827e54a97bfc99b9a77942a</data>
