<node id="Annual Report">
  <data key="d0">Annual Report</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">The Annual Report is an annual publication that includes the financial statements and related disclosures for a company, providing a comprehensive view of its financial health and operations.&lt;SEP&gt;The Annual Report is an annual publication by the company that provides detailed financial and operational information for the year.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f5952f8b9b70d6c7a8ac3693a20d7033&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d780eacfb91e291d22055bf3aca31fa3</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777307810</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Accounting Standards Codification 606">
  <data key="d0">Accounting Standards Codification 606</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Accounting Standards Codification 606, also known as Revenue from Contracts with Customers ("ASC 606"), is a standard that guides the revenue recognition process for companies, focusing on recognizing revenue when control of a product or service is transferred to a customer.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f5952f8b9b70d6c7a8ac3693a20d7033</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777262483</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Determination of distinct performance obligations">
  <data key="d0">Determination of distinct performance obligations</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">The process of determining distinct performance obligations involves identifying separate goods or services within a contract that a company must deliver to a customer, each of which is treated as a separate performance obligation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f5952f8b9b70d6c7a8ac3693a20d7033</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777262483</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Evaluation of the standalone selling price">
  <data key="d0">Evaluation of the standalone selling price</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">The evaluation of the standalone selling price (SSP) is a method used to estimate the price at which a product or service would be sold individually, which is crucial for revenue recognition under ASC 606.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f5952f8b9b70d6c7a8ac3693a20d7033</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777262483</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Assessment of contract combination criteria">
  <data key="d0">Assessment of contract combination criteria</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">The assessment of contract combination criteria is a process used to determine whether multiple contracts with the same customer should be combined into a single contract for accounting purposes.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f5952f8b9b70d6c7a8ac3693a20d7033</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777262483</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Estimates on Sales-Based Royalty Revenue Accruals">
  <data key="d0">Estimates on Sales-Based Royalty Revenue Accruals</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Estimates on Sales-Based Royalty Revenue Accruals involve predicting the amount of royalties to be earned based on the sales of licensed products, taking into account various factors such as market conditions and historical data.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f5952f8b9b70d6c7a8ac3693a20d7033</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777262483</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Valuation of Equity Investments Measured at Fair Value">
  <data key="d0">Valuation of Equity Investments Measured at Fair Value</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">The Valuation of Equity Investments Measured at Fair Value is a method used to estimate the fair value of non-marketable securities, which are investments in enterprises that are not publicly traded.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f5952f8b9b70d6c7a8ac3693a20d7033</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777262483</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Non-marketable securities">
  <data key="d0">Non-marketable securities</data>
  <data key="d1">financialdata</data>
  <data key="d2">Non-marketable securities are investments in unlisted early-stage development enterprises, which may be valued using the NAV practical expedient, representing the estimated fair value of these investments.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f5952f8b9b70d6c7a8ac3693a20d7033</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777262483</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Estimates and assumptions">
  <data key="d0">Estimates and assumptions</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Estimates and assumptions are the foundational calculations and presuppositions used in financial reporting, which are integral to the preparation of financial statements.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f5952f8b9b70d6c7a8ac3693a20d7033</data>
