<node id="ASC 606">
  <data key="d0">ASC 606</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">ASC 606, or Revenue from Contracts with Customers, is a revenue recognition concept that dictates when and how revenue is recognized upon transferring control of products or services to customers.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f5952f8b9b70d6c7a8ac3693a20d7033</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777262484</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Licensing Arrangements">
  <data key="d0">Licensing Arrangements</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Licensing Arrangements refer to the contractual agreements that grant customers the right to use a company's intellectual property, goods, or services, often involving distinct performance obligations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f5952f8b9b70d6c7a8ac3693a20d7033</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777262484</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Forward-looking Information">
  <data key="d0">Forward-looking Information</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Forward-looking Information encompasses predictions and expectations about future events, which are used in determining performance obligations and estimating standalone selling prices.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f5952f8b9b70d6c7a8ac3693a20d7033</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777262484</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Support, Maintenance Services, and Training Services">
  <data key="d0">Support, Maintenance Services, and Training Services</data>
  <data key="d1">service</data>
  <data key="d2">Support, Maintenance Services, and Training Services are types of services provided by a company, often with observable market prices used to determine the standalone selling price.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f5952f8b9b70d6c7a8ac3693a20d7033</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777262484</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Residual Approach">
  <data key="d0">Residual Approach</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">The Residual Approach is a method used to allocate the transaction price to performance obligations when the standalone selling price is not directly observable.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f5952f8b9b70d6c7a8ac3693a20d7033</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777262484</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Cost-Plus Margin Approach">
  <data key="d0">Cost-Plus Margin Approach</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">The Cost-Plus Margin Approach is a method for estimating the standalone selling price based on the cost of the product plus an expected margin.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f5952f8b9b70d6c7a8ac3693a20d7033</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777262484</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Macroeconomic Effects">
  <data key="d0">Macroeconomic Effects</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Macroeconomic Effects are the influences of large-scale economic factors on financial estimates and business operations, such as geopolitical issues and natural disasters.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f5952f8b9b70d6c7a8ac3693a20d7033</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777262484</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Historical Data">
  <data key="d0">Historical Data</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Historical Data refers to past records and statistics that are used in making financial estimates and judgments, particularly in the context of royalty revenue accruals.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f5952f8b9b70d6c7a8ac3693a20d7033</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777262484</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Income Tax Benefit (Expense)">
  <data key="d0">Income Tax Benefit (Expense)</data>
  <data key="d1">category</data>
  <data key="d2">Income tax benefit (expense) is accounted for using the asset and liability method under GAAP, recognizing deferred income taxes for temporary differences between financial statement carrying amounts and tax basis of assets and liabilities.&lt;SEP&gt;Income Tax Benefit (Expense) is a financial concept representing the difference between income tax expenses and benefits recognized in the financial statements under GAAP.&lt;SEP&gt;Income Tax Benefit (Expense) is a category that decreased by 23% for the company in the fiscal year ended March 31, 2025.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1bd342ebc79b6c8d6a4c0db7019159b3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5b11abf58ed4d75a128d8d943d08096f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8b7994a7b9c5c9289cc48f3afe48287c</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777262484</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="U.K.'s &quot;patent box&quot; regime">
  <data key="d0">U.K.'s "patent box" regime</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The U.K.'s "patent box" regime is a tax policy that allows certain profits attributable to revenue from patented products to be taxed at a reduced corporation tax rate of 10%.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1bd342ebc79b6c8d6a4c0db7019159b3</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777262484</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Consolidated Income Statements">
  <data key="d0">Consolidated Income Statements</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">The Consolidated Income Statements are financial reports that compile the income, expenses, and profits of a company and its subsidiaries over a specific period.&lt;SEP&gt;The Consolidated Income Statements are financial reports where the impact of revisions of original estimates is recognized.&gt;&lt;SEP&gt;The Consolidated Income Statements is where changes in the allowance for deferred tax assets are recognized.&gt;</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1bd342ebc79b6c8d6a4c0db7019159b3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8e2d85f7a44ae4d46a5296c95183929c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1fc03c6340e9f91435287101b7ba57e5</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777262484</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="U.K.">
  <data key="d0">U.K.</data>
  <data key="d1">location</data>
  <data key="d2">The U.K. is a jurisdiction where the company conducts business and is subject to income taxes.&lt;SEP&gt;The U.K. is a country in Europe where the company conducts business and is subject to the "patent box" tax regime.&lt;SEP&gt;The U.K. is a location where legislation was enacted to implement the OECD's Pillar Two framework.&lt;SEP&gt;The U.K. is a country that enacted legislation to implement the OECD's Pillar Two framework.|&lt;SEP&gt;The U.K. is a location where the company has significant manufacturing operations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1bd342ebc79b6c8d6a4c0db7019159b3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5b11abf58ed4d75a128d8d943d08096f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-13f18e1b9ab8662fc4105918eb9e67e8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8b7994a7b9c5c9289cc48f3afe48287c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f20aa9a81d6ab585196c52c4b81c36f5</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777307376</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
