  <data key="d0">Revenue from external customers</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Revenue from external customers represents the income generated from customers outside the company, constituting the majority of total revenue.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1bd342ebc79b6c8d6a4c0db7019159b3</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777262484</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Revenue from related parties">
  <data key="d0">Revenue from related parties</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Revenue from related parties represents income generated from transactions with parties that have a relationship with the company, constituting a portion of total revenue.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1bd342ebc79b6c8d6a4c0db7019159b3</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777262484</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Total revenue">
  <data key="d0">Total revenue</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Total revenue is the overall income generated by the company from all sources, including both external customers and related parties.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1bd342ebc79b6c8d6a4c0db7019159b3</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777262484</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Cost of sales">
  <data key="d0">Cost of sales</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Cost of sales refers to the direct costs attributable to the production of goods or services sold by the company.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1bd342ebc79b6c8d6a4c0db7019159b3</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777262484</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Gross profit (loss)">
  <data key="d0">Gross profit (loss)</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Gross profit (loss) is the amount remaining after subtracting the cost of sales from total revenue, indicating the company's profitability from its primary operations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1bd342ebc79b6c8d6a4c0db7019159b3</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777262484</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Operating expenses">
  <data key="d0">Operating expenses</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Operating expenses include all costs related to the company's operations, excluding cost of sales.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1bd342ebc79b6c8d6a4c0db7019159b3</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777262484</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Research and development">
  <data key="d0">Research and development</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Research and development expenses represent the funds allocated to developing new products or improving existing ones.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1bd342ebc79b6c8d6a4c0db7019159b3</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777262484</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Selling, general and administrative">
  <data key="d0">Selling, general and administrative</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Selling, general and administrative expenses cover all marketing, administrative, and general costs incurred by the company.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1bd342ebc79b6c8d6a4c0db7019159b3</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777262484</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Disposal, restructuring and other operating expenses, net">
  <data key="d0">Disposal, restructuring and other operating expenses, net</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Disposal, restructuring and other operating expenses, net include one-time costs associated with restructuring and disposal activities.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1bd342ebc79b6c8d6a4c0db7019159b3</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777262484</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Operating income (loss)">
  <data key="d0">Operating income (loss)</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Operating income (loss) is the profit or loss left after deducting operating expenses from gross profit.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1bd342ebc79b6c8d6a4c0db7019159b3</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777262484</data>
