  <data key="d0">Bureau of Industry and Security</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Bureau of Industry and Security, referred to as BIS, is a part of the U.S. Department of Commerce that extended the reach of U.S. export controls on the semiconductor industry.&gt;&lt;SEP&gt;The Bureau of Industry and Security is a government agency that issues rules and regulations affecting international trade.&lt;SEP&gt;The Bureau of Industry and Security (BIS) is the U.S. government agency responsible for imposing export controls and regulations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d028a96cd827e54a97bfc99b9a77942a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6430e92774e5a3f258ef2544910d4dd5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-db3fcbe26ec52d22abad5f9f0435fea6</data>
