<node id="Impairment Charge">
  <data key="d0">Impairment Charge</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The impairment charge is a financial accounting term referring to the recognition of a loss due to the decline in value of long-lived assets.&lt;SEP&gt;An impairment charge is a reduction in the value of an asset for financial reporting purposes, reflecting a decrease in future earnings potential.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-37906de44c22f23501372f2b90cd5aa7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-25056dc4aba0a40a47c338bbf9630c33</data>
