<node id="Agentic AI">
  <data key="d0">Agentic AI</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Agentic AI refers to the shift in AI from training models to deploying continuously running agents that reason, plan, and act, driving a major inflection point in global computing and increasing the demand for CPUs.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-2d1f6742e80ed84d267cfe46fa7c9e31</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777308127</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Arm Compute Subsystems">
  <data key="d0">Arm Compute Subsystems</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Arm Compute Subsystems (CSS) are part of Arm's platform strategy, providing partners with options to build on Arm technology and enabling faster innovation across the AI ecosystem.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-2d1f6742e80ed84d267cfe46fa7c9e31</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777308127</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Arm Neoverse V3">
  <data key="d0">Arm Neoverse V3</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">The Arm Neoverse V3 cores are a component of the Arm AGI CPU, delivering leading performance per core, SoC, blade, and rack, with 6GB/s memory bandwidth per core at sub-100ns latency.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-2d1f6742e80ed84d267cfe46fa7c9e31</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777308127</data>
